    <!--navbar-->
    <div class="container">
        <header id="header">
            <h1 style="text-align: center;"><i class="fas fa-chess-rook"></i> Golkonda Fort</h1>
            <p>The historic fortress of Hyderabad</p>
            <div class="hyderabad-badge">
                <i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Hyderabad, Telangana, India
            </div>
        </header>

        <div class="main-image-container">
            <img src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/R.064f2b98c3026cb037c9f3b468292fd1?rik=1Y4WCsTJseakjQ&riu=http%3a%2f%2f3.bp.blogspot.com%2f-y62A9HnXRr4%2fU7f8wnsQFeI%2fAAAAAAAABq4%2fbxFT15Bc1Xk%2fs1600%2fGolconda-Fort.jpg&ehk=7Oasvei5%2bDyeDf8H3r9lDRcQ2ng8enuiBLSiYeOfEa0%3d&risl=&pid=ImgRaw&r=0"
                alt="Golkonda Fort" class="main-image">
            <div class="image-overlay">
                <h2>"The Citadel of Splendor"</h2>
                <p>Capital of the Qutb Shahi Dynasty</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <section class="description" id="description">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-history"></i> Historical Significance</h2>
            <p>Golkonda Fort is a historic fortress in Hyderabad, known for its impressive architecture, strategic location, and rich history. It was once the capital of the Qutb Shahi dynasty and is famous for its acoustic system, grand gates, and diamond trade legacy, including the Koh-i-Noor diamond.</p>

            <div class="historical-fact">
                Originally built as a mud fort in the 13th century by the Kakatiya dynasty, it was later fortified by the Qutb Shahi rulers in the 16th century. The fort's acoustic system allows whispers at the entrance to be heard at the highest point, a marvel of engineering.
            </div>

            <p>The fort is a popular tourist destination, offering panoramic views of Hyderabad, light and sound shows narrating its history, and exploration of its palaces, mosques, and royal chambers. It remains a symbol of Hyderabad's glorious past.</p>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 20px; color: var(--hyderabad-blue);"><i class="fas fa-archway"></i> Key Features</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                <li>Acoustic system for communication across the fort</li>
                <li>Eight grand gates and a 10-km outer wall</li>
                <li>Royal palaces, mosques, and audience halls</li>
                <li>Evening light and sound show in multiple languages</li>
                <li>Strategic hilltop location with scenic views</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <div class="nearby-section">
            <section class="restaurants" id="restaurants">
                <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-utensils"></i> Nearby Restaurants</h2>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.g9qeedgiUp667Kzo7MlUJwHaEo?rs=1&pid=ImgDetMain"
                            alt="Golconda Pavilion" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-utensils"></i> Golconda Pavilion</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Somajiguda (4 km from fort)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 12:00 PM - 11:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Avg. Price for Two:</span> ₹600–₹800
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.AkPZjKrssz5oovgT1YSm_gHaEO?rs=1&pid=ImgDetMain"
                            alt="Bawarchi Restaurant" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-utensils"></i> Bawarchi Restaurant</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> RTC X Roads (5 km from fort)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 11:00 AM - 11:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Avg. Price for Two:</span> ₹700–₹900
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.ixfrQGE9_9qOMDuobjfApQHaJ3?rs=1&pid=ImgDetMain"
                            alt="The Fisherman’s Wharf" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-utensils"></i> The Fisherman’s Wharf</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Banjara Hills (6 km from fort)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 12:00 PM - 11:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Avg. Price for Two:</span> ₹800–₹1,000
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP._maCSwU4gwoVnvf_VCaOXQHaJ4?rs=1&pid=ImgDetMain"
                            alt="Shilparamam Restaurant" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-utensils"></i> Shilparamam Restaurant</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Madhapur (6 km from fort)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 10:00 AM - 10:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Avg. Price for Two:</span> ₹500–₹700
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/1b/29/8d/c6/paradise-restaurant-in.jpg"
                            alt="Paradise Restaurant" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-utensils"></i> Paradise Restaurant</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Secunderabad (8 km from fort)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 11:00 AM - 11:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Avg. Price for Two:</span> ₹700–₹1,000
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="famous-places" id="attractions">
                <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-map-marked-alt"></i> Nearby Attractions</h2>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://myweekendtrips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Qutub-Shahi-Tombs-Hyderabad1.jpg"
                            alt="Qutb Shahi Tombs" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-archway"></i> Qutb Shahi Tombs</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-walking"></i> 2 km from Golkonda Fort</div>
                    <p>Royal necropolis with grand mausoleums of Qutb Shahi rulers.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://www.hyderabadtourism.travel/images/places-to-visit/headers/shilparamam-hyderabad-tourism-entry-fee-timings-holidays-reviews-header.jpg"
                            alt="Shilparamam" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-palette"></i> Shilparamam</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-car"></i> 6 km from Golkonda Fort</div>
                    <p>Cultural village showcasing arts, crafts, and performances.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/R.923e0d68897445dae606e29c4384e971?rik=b23uPl%2bUPgyyfQ&riu=http%3a%2f%2fhyderabadtourism.co.in%2fwp-content%2fuploads%2f2024%2f06%2fTaramati-Baradari.jpg&ehk=OtnRLUvQjVVaB%2bCBVm4f1DlAMjPDugefo8%2biiU0egIg%3d&risl=&pid=ImgRaw&r=0"
                            alt="Taramati Baradari" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-archway"></i> Taramati Baradari</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-car"></i> 4 km from Golkonda Fort</div>
                    <p>Historic pavilion with scenic views and cultural events.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.pND-4MR3Rb0RmW50sSpE4gHaFj?rs=1&pid=ImgDetMain"
                            alt="Banjara Hills" class="place-image">
